<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="R7-093" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Audit Playbook Library Code Page modal current routing</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <wave>9</wave>
    <estimated-effort>2-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>audit, code-page, wave-9</tags>
    <rigor-level>STANDARD</rigor-level>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <fr-coverage>FR-18 (audit portion)</fr-coverage>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    FR-18 requires wiring the Playbook Library modal into 3 consumer surfaces (spaarke-ai chat,
    briefing widget, ad-hoc launcher). Before wiring (tasks 094-096), audit the current state of
    the Playbook Library: does the modal exist? Where is it (Code Page, shared component, both)?
    Is it routed from any consumer today? What is its contract (props, expected callbacks)?
    Produce an audit doc that tasks 094-096 can follow without re-reading source.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React / Power Platform developer familiar with Spaarke Code Pages, the
    Spaarke.UI.Components shared library, and the consumer-routing model. Goal: extract the
    current modal contract + wire-up state, not modify anything yet.
  </role>

  <goal>
    An audit document at `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/playbook-library-audit.md`
    that answers:
    1. Where does the Playbook Library modal live today? (PlaybookLibraryPage at external-spa,
       PlaybookLibraryShell at Spaarke.UI.Components, or both? Document file paths + roles.)
    2. What is the modal's public contract — props, callbacks, expected payload to launch a playbook?
    3. What consumer surfaces (if any) currently route to it today? Audit: spaarke-ai chat surface
       (src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/), Daily Briefing widget (src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/),
       LegalWorkspace ad-hoc launchers, any other.
    4. How does the modal list playbooks? Does it query sprk_analysisplaybook directly, consume an
       endpoint, or use Xrm.WebApi?
    5. How does the modal launch a playbook today (if it does)? Direct PlaybookOrchestrationService
       call, IInvokePlaybookAi, or some other path? Confirm it eventually flows through Path A.5
       routing (consumer code -> IConsumerRoutingService -> IInvokePlaybookAi).
    6. For each of the 3 target consumer surfaces (tasks 094-096), identify the natural mount point
       for a "Browse Playbooks" affordance — file path + component name.
    7. What is the modal's intended UX — list every playbook + its consumer mapping (per FR-18
       acceptance criterion)? If the modal lists playbooks without showing consumer mapping today,
       note this as a gap tasks 094-096 may need to close.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="design-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="library-page">src/client/external-spa/src/pages/PlaybookLibraryPage.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="library-shell-component">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/PlaybookLibraryShell/PlaybookLibraryShell.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="spaarke-ai-app">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/App.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="spaarke-ai-conversation">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/conversation/ConversationPane.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="briefing-widget">src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/src/components/DailyBriefingApp.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="canonical-doc">docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">BFF AI Architecture — Playbook Library invocations MUST flow through IInvokePlaybookAi triangle (canonical). Audit confirms or flags gap.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-18">Acceptance: at least 3 consumer surfaces have "Browse Playbooks" affordance; modal lists every playbook WITH consumer mapping; clicking a playbook invokes it through proper Path A.5 routing.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Audit task — modification justification triple applies to tasks 094-096 (the wire-up tasks), not this audit.</constraint>
    <constraint source="MUST NOT modify">docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md — READ-ONLY in R7.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>code-pages/playbook-library</topic>
    <files>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-013-bff-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-COMPONENT-MODEL.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/ai-architecture-consumer-routing.md</file>
      <file>docs/standards/DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="PlaybookLibraryShell shared component" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/PlaybookLibraryShell/">
        Shared lib component — likely the modal body. Audit: is it a Dialog or an inline shell?
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="PlaybookLibraryPage external-spa" location="src/client/external-spa/src/pages/PlaybookLibraryPage.tsx">
        Standalone page route — likely a non-modal mount. Audit: is this the routed page or the modal?
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-18 was identified in design.md as a gap: the modal exists (shared component or external-spa
      page) but isn't routed from the in-flow consumer surfaces (spaarke-ai chat, briefing widget,
      ad-hoc launchers). Users currently have no in-flow path to "browse + invoke any playbook" from
      these consumer UIs. Tasks 094-096 close this. This audit task scopes the work and identifies
      the natural mount points before any code changes.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="none" status="parallel">Can run in parallel with tasks 090-092 (the orchestrator migration); FR-18 is independent of FR-17 except for shared design context.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 092 (Wave 9) — adds the chat-summarize row to sprk_playbookconsumer. The Library modal's "consumer mapping" column reads this table.</item>
      <item>Task 067 (Wave 6) — author docs/guides/ai-guide-consumer-wiring.md uses the Library modal as a maker discoverability surface.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: STANDARD · 📋 REASON: audit-only task, no source modification, planning artifact only · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context">
      Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md (FR-18) + plan.md (Wave 9).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Read PlaybookLibraryShell shared component">
      Open src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/PlaybookLibraryShell/PlaybookLibraryShell.tsx
      and any sibling files. Document: props, callbacks, internal state, how it lists playbooks
      (data source: BFF endpoint vs Xrm.WebApi vs hardcoded), how it launches a playbook (callback
      to host, direct API call, or routing config).
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Read PlaybookLibraryPage external-spa">
      Open src/client/external-spa/src/pages/PlaybookLibraryPage.tsx. Document: route mount point,
      relationship to PlaybookLibraryShell (consumer / wrapper / duplicate?), launch flow.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Audit spaarke-ai chat surface mount opportunities">
      Read src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/App.tsx + ConversationPane.tsx + WelcomePanel.tsx +
      ChatHistoryPanel.tsx. Identify: where would a "Browse Playbooks" affordance naturally mount?
      A button in the toolbar? An item in CommandHelpPanel? A slash command in ConversationPane?
      Recommend 1-2 candidate mount points for task 094.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Audit Daily Briefing widget mount opportunities">
      Read src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/src/components/DailyBriefingApp.tsx
      (+ surrounding files in same directory). Identify: where would a "Browse Playbooks"
      affordance naturally mount? Recommend 1-2 candidate mount points for task 095.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Audit ad-hoc launcher candidates">
      Examine LegalWorkspace + any other ad-hoc playbook launcher. Glob for "ad-hoc" / "playbook"
      / "invoke" components in src/client/. Identify a candidate launcher surface that would
      naturally host a "Browse Playbooks" affordance. Recommend 1 candidate for task 096.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Map playbook listing data source">
      Trace how PlaybookLibraryShell lists playbooks. If it uses Xrm.WebApi, document whether that
      complies with DATA-ACCESS-DECISION-CRITERIA.md. If it uses a BFF endpoint, document the
      endpoint path and whether it exposes consumer mappings. If listing-with-consumer-mapping is
      NOT yet supported, flag this as a gap tasks 094-096 may need to close (likely a small BFF
      endpoint addition — call this out for downstream task scoping).
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Trace playbook launch path">
      Trace what happens when the user clicks a playbook in PlaybookLibraryShell. Document the call
      chain. Confirm it eventually flows through IInvokePlaybookAi (Path A.5). If it bypasses
      Path A.5, flag as gap.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Write audit document">
      Create notes/spikes/playbook-library-audit.md answering the 7 goal questions. Include:
      - File map (PlaybookLibraryShell + PlaybookLibraryPage roles + relationship)
      - Public contract / props / callbacks of the Shell component
      - Current routing state (which consumers route to it today — likely "none in-flow")
      - Recommended mount points per consumer surface (1-2 candidates for spaarke-ai, briefing, ad-hoc)
      - Playbook listing data source + any gaps (esp. consumer-mapping column)
      - Launch path: confirmed Path A.5 OR gap to close
      Target: 150-220 lines.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Update current-task.md + TASK-INDEX">
      Mark task 093 status complete; advance current-task.md to task 094.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Commit">
      Commit notes/spikes/playbook-library-audit.md with conventional message.
      Example: docs(r7/wave9): audit Playbook Library modal current routing state (task 093, FR-18)
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read (PlaybookLibrary files, consumer surfaces, canonical docs)</tool>
    <tool>Grep (search for PlaybookLibrary mounts, "Browse Playbooks" strings, consumer-routing wiring)</tool>
    <tool>Glob (find ad-hoc launcher candidates)</tool>
    <tool>Write (audit document)</tool>
    <tool>Bash (git commit)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="document">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/playbook-library-audit.md</output>
    <output type="state-update">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/current-task.md (advance to task 094)</output>
    <output type="state-update">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md (mark 093 ✅)</output>
    <output type="commit">docs(r7/wave9): audit Playbook Library modal current routing state (task 093, FR-18)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Audit document exists at notes/spikes/playbook-library-audit.md</criterion>
    <criterion>Document answers all 7 goal questions explicitly</criterion>
    <criterion>Document maps PlaybookLibraryShell + PlaybookLibraryPage roles + relationship</criterion>
    <criterion>Document captures the modal's props/callbacks/contract</criterion>
    <criterion>Document recommends 1-2 mount points per consumer surface (spaarke-ai, briefing, ad-hoc)</criterion>
    <criterion>Document confirms (or flags gap with) playbook listing data source + consumer-mapping column availability</criterion>
    <criterion>Document confirms (or flags gap with) launch flow going through IInvokePlaybookAi / Path A.5</criterion>
    <criterion>current-task.md updated to point at task 094 as next</criterion>
    <criterion>TASK-INDEX.md shows 093 ✅, 094 🔲 ready</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
